IN	1 teaspoon garlic powder
IN	1 teaspoon onion powder
IN	1 teaspoon paprika
IN	1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
IN	1/2 teaspoon fine sea salt
IN	1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper
IN	2 large Yukon Gold potatoes, unpeeled, sliced into 1/2-inch slices, ends discarded
IN	2 large red potatoes, unpeeled, sliced into 1/2-inch slices, ends discarded
IN	2 sweet potatoes, peeled, sliced into 1/2-inch slices, ends discarded
IN	1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil
IN	Fine sea salt
IN	Fresh rosemary sprigs
PR	Preheat oven to 400Â°F.
PR	Cover a large jelly-roll pan or cookie sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.
PR	In a small bowl, mix garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, black pepper, salt, and cayenne. Set aside.
PR	Place all the sliced potatoes into a large mixing bowl.
PR	Pour the oil into the bowl. Toss to coat. Sprinkle in the spice blend. Toss to coat well. Arrange the potatoes in a single layer on prepared baking sheet. Roast the potatoes, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
PR	Season with a sprinkle of salt.
PR	Make layered stacks using the three kinds of potatoes. Press a rosemary skewer through the center to secure each stack. Serve hot.
